0.1 Figure 1C - UMAP representation of integrated analysis

#load packages
library(dplyr) #tidyverse dataframe manipulation
library(Seurat) #scRNAseq analysis
library(patchwork) #organizes plots
library(fcoex) #coexpression
library(ComplexHeatmap) #for making heatmaps
library(magick) #rasterize heatmap


#load integrated object
load(file = "forebrain_all_final.RObj")

forebrain.integrated <- RenameIdents(object = forebrain.integrated, `UnK` = "NK-like")
forebrain.integrated <- RenameIdents(object = forebrain.integrated, `Astrocytes` = "Astrocyte-like")

levels <- c('dHabenula', 'vHabenula', 'Microglia', 'OPC', 'Oligodendrocytes', 'Olfactory Bulb',
            'Progenitor_02', 'Progenitor_01','NK-like', 'Epithelial/Endothelial Cells', 'Cycling progenitors_01', 'Cycling progenitors_02', 
            'Committed_pallium_precursors', 'Committed_subpallium_precursors', 
            'Pallium_IN01', 'Pallium_IN02', 'Subpallium_IN', 'Subpallium_03',
            'Pallium_01', 'Pallium_02', 'Pallium_03', 'Pallium_04', 'Pallium_05', 'Pallium_06', 'Pallium_07', 'Pallium_08', 'Pallium_09',
            'Subpallium_01', 'Subpallium_02', 'PoA_02', 'Subpallium_04', 'Subpallium_05', 'Subpallium_06', 
            'Subpallium_07', 'Subpallium_08', 'PoA_01', 'Astrocyte-like','Pallium_IN03')

Idents(forebrain.integrated) <- factor(x = Idents(forebrain.integrated), levels = levels)

#recoloring clusters
cols <- c('grey', 'grey64', 'mistyrose2', 'chartreuse1' , 'chocolate3', 'deepskyblue1', 
          'rosybrown3','gold1', 'orange1', 'sandybrown', 'coral', 'navajowhite1',
          'lightsteelblue2', 'darkseagreen1', 
          'lightcyan1', 'darkslategray1', 'pink1', 'thistle1',
          'cyan4', 'blue1', 'darkturquoise', 'yellowgreen', 'mediumspringgreen', 'lightskyblue', 'royalblue1', 'green1', 'magenta1',
          'purple','lightcoral', 'orchid1', 'palevioletred1', 'darkviolet', 'maroon1', 
          'tomato1', 'slateblue1','red','burlywood2','olivedrab1')
cols <- lapply(cols, adjustcolor, alpha= 1.0)

#plot with new colors
DimPlot(forebrain.integrated, cols = cols, label = F, pt.size = 0.6, split.by="age")

#plot without legends
DimPlot(forebrain.integrated, cols = cols, label = F, pt.size = 0.6) + NoLegend() + NoAxes()

#rename gene
rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$integrated@data)[rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$integrated@data) == "NP5"] <- "c16h2orf66"

rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$RNA@counts
)[rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$RNA@counts
) == "NP5"] <- "c16h2orf66"

rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$RNA@data
)[rownames(forebrain.integrated@assays$RNA@data
) == "NP5"] <- "c16h2orf66"

0.3 Subpallium dotplot for adult

Tac1 expression in subpallium_02 is easier to see in the dotplot with cells from all ages, but similarity of marker genes between Subpallium_08 and Subpallium_05 is easier to see in the adult only dotplot.

#subset object to only include adult cells
ADULT <- subset(forebrain.integrated, subset = age == "Adult")

#subset object to only include mature neuronal clusters

0.4 Subpallium heat map

#clusters to include in heat map
neuronaldpfad <- c("Subpallium_01", "Subpallium_02", "Subpallium_03", "Subpallium_04", "Subpallium_05", "Subpallium_06", "Subpallium_07", "Subpallium_08")

#subset forebrain.integrated to include selected clusters
neuronad <- subset(forebrain.integrated, subset = clusterInterp2 == neuronaldpfad)

#genes to include in heatmap 
all_markers <- c("dlx1a", "dlx2a", "dlx2b", "dlx5a", "dlx6a", "tbr1b", "neurod1", "nkx2.1", "lhx6", "sst1.1", "npy", "sox6", "etv1", "nxph1", "pvalb6", "lhx8a", "gbx1", "calb1", "isl1", "zic1", "zic2a", "zic4", "zic5", "slc17a6b", "slc32a1", "slc6a1b", "gad1b", "gad2", "tac1", "sp8a", "synpr", "pyyb", "penkb", "six3b", "pyya", "cxcl14", "foxp1b", "rgs4", "ncaldb", "c16h2orf66", "prdm12b", "si:ch73-386o14.1", "gfra2b", "drd2b","nr2f2", "prox1a", "prox1b", "calb2a", "calb2b", "vip", "satb2")

#make a matrix with data for selected genes
mat<- neuronad[["RNA"]]@data[all_markers, ] %>% as.matrix()

## scale the rows
mat<- t(scale(t(mat)))

#remove NAs
mat <- mat[!rowSums(is.na(mat)),]

#add the cluster name information
cluster_anno<- neuronad@meta.data$clusterInterp2

# what's the value range in the matrix?
quantile(mat, c(0.1, 0.95))
##        10%        95% 
## -0.4645979  2.1911593

## [15] "#6A006A" "#600060" "#550055" "#4A004A" "#400040" "#350035" "#2B002B"

## [50] "#FFFF00"
## make the black color map to 0. the yellow map to highest and the purle map to the lowest
col_fun = circlize::colorRamp2(c(-1, 0, 3), c("#FF00FF", "black", "#FFFF00"))

#make a heatmap
p1 <- Heatmap(mat, name = "Expression",  
        column_split = factor(cluster_anno),
        cluster_columns = TRUE,
        show_column_dend = TRUE,
        cluster_column_slices = TRUE,
        column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 8),
        column_gap = unit(0.5, "mm"),
        cluster_rows = FALSE,
        show_row_dend = FALSE,
        col = col_fun,
        row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 9),
        column_title_rot = 90,
        top_annotation = HeatmapAnnotation(foo = anno_block(gp = gpar(fill = scales::hue_pal()(9)))),
        show_column_names = FALSE,
        use_raster = FALSE)

0.7 Find markers that are coexpressed with c1ql3b.1

#split object into cells <1 and >2 
lowc1ql3b <- subset(neuronad, subset = c1ql3b.1 < 1)
highc1ql3b.1 <- subset(neuronad, subset = c1ql3b.1 > 2)
both <- subset(neuronad, subset = c1ql3b.1 > 2 | c1ql3b.1 < 1)

#add metadata to objects
lowc1ql3b$c1ql3level <- c("lowc1ql3b")
highc1ql3b.1$c1ql3level <- c("highc1ql3b")

#merge objects
c1ql3bobject <- merge(lowc1ql3b, y = c(highc1ql3b.1))

#set new ident to c1ql3 level
c1ql3bobject <- SetIdent(c1ql3bobject, value = c1ql3bobject$c1ql3level)

#add reductions to new object
c1ql3bobject@reductions <- both@reductions

#plot UMAP
DimPlot(c1ql3bobject, reduction = "umap", raster=FALSE, label=T, repel=T)

#find markers
#c1ql3bmarkers <- FindAllMarkers(c1ql3bobject, only.pos = T, logfc.threshold = 0.65)
